amulog/example — third-party data and code attribution
=======================================================

This directory bundles small (2,000-line) log samples from the loghub
collection and amulog template definitions derived from its ground truth,
together with parser scripts from log2seq, so that amulog can be tried on open
log data out of the box.

loghub log samples and derived templates (CC BY 4.0)
----------------------------------------------------
The `<Name>_2k.log` samples are taken from the loghub collection / logparser
benchmark and redistributed here under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International License (CC BY 4.0): https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

The `<Name>.tpl` files are amulog template definitions *derived from* loghub's
ground-truth templates (`<Name>_2k.log_templates.csv`), re-expressed in amulog's
own segmented lt-import format; the original CSVs are not redistributed here.
The same CC BY 4.0 attribution applies to these derivatives.

  - loghub: A Large Collection of System Log Datasets for AI-driven Log
    Analytics. Jieming Zhu, Shilin He, Pinjia He, Jinyang Liu, Michael R. Lyu.
    ISSRE 2023.  https://github.com/logpai/loghub
  - Tools and Benchmarks for Automated Log Parsing (the 2k ground truth).
    Jieming Zhu, Shilin He, Jinyang Liu, Pinjia He, Qi Xie, Zibin Zheng,
    Michael R. Lyu. ICSE-SEIP 2019.  https://github.com/logpai/logparser

Several datasets originate from earlier publications; please cite the original
source when using them, in particular:

  - BGL, Thunderbird: Alert Detection in System Logs. Adam Oliner, Jon Stearley.
    DSN 2007. (Supercomputer RAS logs.)
  - HDFS: Detecting Large-Scale System Problems by Mining Console Logs.
    Wei Xu, Ling Huang, Armando Fox, David Patterson, Michael I. Jordan.
    SOSP 2009.

log2seq parser scripts
----------------------
Each `parser.py` is copied from the corresponding log2seq example
(`log2seq/example/loghub_<Name>/parser.py`) and defines the header/statement
parsing rules amulog uses via `manager.parser_script`.
log2seq: https://github.com/amulog/log2seq

Notes
-----
- Only the 2k samples are bundled. Full datasets (multi-GB) are obtained from
  loghub and are never committed here.
- See README.md for the build/verification status of each dataset.
